How Kash solves the problem of ‚Äúdead markets‚Äù in forecasts

There is an old but painful problem in the world of prediction markets ‚Äúdead markets‚Äù. These are markets that never reach their logical conclusion. You can place your bet, freeze liquidity, wait for the result and then it turns out that:
> the event was not verified
> the arbitrators did not respond
> or simply no one has decided ‚Äúwhat really happened‚Äù
Such markets remain ‚Äúsuspended‚Äù, and users‚Äô money gets stuck in a smart contract.

Here are some reasons why ‚Äúdead markets" arise
> The human factor moderators do not have time or forget to close the market.
> Unclear wording for example, ‚Äúwill the new token be successful?‚Äù how to measure it?
> Lack of a reliable data source to confirm the result.
> Low trader activity the market simply loses interest, and no one takes on the role of ‚Äúsolver‚Äù.
As a result, the ecosystem is filled with ‚Äúhanging‚Äù markets, where there are no winners or settlements, and user trust falls.

In Kash, the problem of dead markets disappears thanks to the combination of AI + zk-proofs + smart contracts.

When the market reaches a deadline, the Kash AI agent itself checks whether the event has occurred, using data from verified sources (via zkTLS). For example:
> If the market is about the price of BTC, it pulls data from CoinGecko or Binance
> If it's a political event, he checks the official results on the government website

After the AI ‚Äã‚Äãreceives the data, the system generates a zero-knowledge proof (zk-proof)  a mathematical proof that the information is true, without revealing the source itself. That is, even if someone wanted to ‚Äútwist‚Äù the data, it is impossible, because the proof has already been generated and verified on the blockchain.

When the proof is verified, the smart contract instantly:
> determines who won the bet
> distributes the reward
> updates the market status to ‚Äúresolved.‚Äù

Why is this revolutionary for Prediction Markets Previously, you could come up with a cool market idea, but you risked it getting ‚Äústuck.‚Äù Now, Kash turns prediction into a living, self-regulating ecosystem, where each market is born, evolves, and closes without human intervention.
